title: Alan Jackson - Everything I Love
description:
Because his singing is solid but unremarkable, Alan Jackson tends to be only as good as his song selection. So on several tracks here--his own composition "Buicks To The Moon," for example, or Tom T. Hall&#039;s slighter-than-it-fancies-itself "Little Bitty"--he isn&#039;t exactly sunk by clunky metaphors and cliched arrangements, but he can&#039;t rise above them either. However, on the title track here, and on the searing, twangy power ballad "Between The Devil And Me," he&#039;s as good as he&#039;s ever been. Which is very good indeed.
